gration page (`langchain-tutorial.md`) is viewed\n535: - **THEN** the document provides:\n536:   - LangChain tool wrapper implementation\n537:   - Agent workflow with code execution\n538:   - Session management in multi-turn conversations\n539:   - Error handling patterns\n540: - **AND** includes runnable code snippets\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## REQ-010: Documentation Navigation and Cross-References\n545: \n546: ### Description\n547: \n548: Ensure documentation has proper navigation structure and cross-references between related topics.\n549: \n550: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: Sidebar navigation configured correctly\n553: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus sidebars configuration at `docs/sidebars.ts`\n554: - **WHEN** the sidebars configuration is viewed\n555: - **THEN** the file includes:\n556:   - `architecture` sidebar with autogenerated directory\n557:   - `api` sidebar with Python SDK and Go Client categories\n558:   - `deployment` sidebar for deployment guides\n559: - **AND** each sidebar category has proper labels and descriptions\n560: \n561: #### Scenario: Architecture to API cross-references exist\n562: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation pages\n563: - **WHEN** an architecture page discusses a component\n564: - **THEN** the page includes Docusaurus links to relevant API documentation:\n565:   - Router architecture → Go Client router endpoints\n566:   - PicoD architecture → Python SDK code execution API\n567:   - CRD architecture → Go Client CRUD operations\n568: - **AND** links use proper Docusaurus link syntax\n569: \n570: #### Scenario: API to deployment cross-references exist\n571: - **GIVEN** the API documentation pages\n572: - **WHEN** an API page documents client configuration\n573: - **THEN** the page links to deployment configuration documentation\n574: - **AND** includes links to Helm value configuration\n575: \n576: #### Scenario: Documentation index page exists\n577: - **GIVEN** the documentation site\n578: - **WHEN** a user visits the documentation root\n579: - **THEN** an index page (`docs/docs/intro.md`) exists\n580: - **AND** the page provides:\n581:   - Overview of AgentCube\n582:   - Quick links to Getting Started, Architecture, API, Deployment\n583:   - Documentation structure diagram\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ## REQ-011: Documentation Quality and Completeness\n588: \n589: ### Description\n590: \n591: Ensure documentation meets quality standards for technical accuracy, readability, and completeness.\n592: \n593: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n594: \n595: #### Scenario: All API methods are documented\n596: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK source code at `sdk-python/`\n597: - **WHEN** documentation generation is verified\n598: - **THEN** every public class method in `CodeInterpreterClient` has a documentation entry\n599: - **AND** every public method in `AgentRuntimeClient` has a documentation entry\n600: - **AND** documentation coverage metric is ≥90%\n601: \n602: #### Scenario: Documentation builds without errors\n603: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus documentation site\n604: - **WHEN** `npm run build` is executed in the `docs/` directory\n605: - **THEN** the build succeeds with no errors\n606: - **AND** all pages are generated correctly\n607: - **AND** no broken internal links are reported\n608: \n609: #### Scenario: Code examples are runnable\n610: - **GIVEN** the documentation code examples\n611: - **WHEN** code examples are tested against a running AgentCube instance\n612: - **THEN** at least 80% of code examples execute successfully\n613: - **AND** examples use realistic parameters and values\n614: - **AND** examples include necessary import statements\n615: \n616: #### Scenario: Documentation is version-controlled\n617: - **GIVEN** the documentation files\n618: - **WHEN** git history is examined\n619: - **THEN** all documentation files are tracked in version control\n620: - **AND** documentation changes are reviewed via pull request process\n621: - **AND** significant documentation updates are mentioned in changelog\n622: \n623: #### Scenario: Documentation has consistent formatting\n624: - **GIVEN** all documentation markdown files\n625: - **WHEN** formatting is validated\n626: - **THEN** all files use consistent markdown style:\n627:   - Headers use ATX style (# syntax)\n628:   - Code blocks have language annotations\n629:   - Tables use GitHub-flavored markdown syntax\n630:   - Lists use consistent indentation (2 spaces)\n631: - **AND** Docusaurus frontmatter (`id`, `title`, `description`) is present where required\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## REQ-012: Internationalization Support\n636: \n637: ### Description\n638: \n639: Provide documentation in multiple languages (English as primary, with structure for translations).\n640: \n641: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n642: \n643: #### Scenario: English documentation is primary\n644: - **GIVEN** the documentation directory\n645: - **WHEN** the default documentation locale is examined\n646: - **THEN** all documentation files are written in English\n647: - **AND** English is configured as default locale in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n648: \n649: #### Scenario: Translation structure exists\n650: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus i18n configuration at `docs/i18n/`\n651: - **WHEN** the i18n directory structure is examined\n652: - **THEN** the directory structure supports translations:\n653:   - `i18n/zh-CN/` for Chinese translation\n654:   - `i18n/ja/` for Japanese translation\n655: - **AND** translation JSON files for UI strings exist\n656: \n657: #### Scenario: Locale configuration is correct\n658: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus config\n659: - **WHEN** `i18n` configuration is examined\n660: - **THEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` includes:\n661:   - `defaultLocale: 'en'`\n662:   - `locales: ['en', 'zh-CN', 'ja']`\n663:   - Locale names and labels configured\n664: - **AND** locale switcher UI is enabled\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## REQ-013: Documentation Search and Indexing\n669: \n670: ### Description\n671: \n672: Enable documentation search functionality for users to find relevant content quickly.\n673: \n674: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n675: \n676: #### Scenario: Documentation search is enabled\n677: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus configuration\n678: - **WHEN** search configuration is examined\n679: - **THEN** a search plugin is configured (e.g., Algolia or local search)\n680: - **AND** search input is visible in documentation navbar\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Search indexes all documentation pages\n683: - **GIVEN** the search configuration\n684: - **WHEN** search functionality is tested\n685: - **THEN** search results include:\n686:   - Architecture documentation pages\n687:   - API documentation pages\n688:   - Deployment guides\n689:   - Getting started pages\n690: - **AND** search results show page titles and relevant excerpts\n691: \n692: #### Scenario: API methods are searchable\n693: - **GIVEN** the documentation search\n694: - **WHEN** a user searches for \"execute_code\"\n695: - **THEN** the search returns results pointing to:\n696:   - Python SDK code execution documentation\n697:   - Code execution flow architecture\n698:   - Quick start tutorial with execute_code example\n699: - **AND** search results are ranked by relevance\n700: \n701: ---\n702: \n703: ## Summary\n704: \n705: | REQ ID | Component | Deliverables |\n706: |--------|-----------|--------------|\n707: | REQ-001 | Architecture Overview | `overview.md` with system diagram and tech stack |\n708: | REQ-002 | Component Architecture | `router.md`, `workloadmanager.md`, `picod.md`, `agentd.md` |\n709: | REQ-003 | Data Flow | Sandbox creation, code execution, session routing flows |\n710: | REQ-004 | Python SDK API | `overview.md`, `code-interpreter-client.md`, `agent-runtime-client.md`, `exceptions.md`, `sessions.md` |\n711: | REQ-005 | Go Client API | `overview.md`, `clientset.md`, CRUD docs, `informer.md`, `testing.md` |\n712: | REQ-006 | CRD Schema | `crd-agent-runtime.md`, `crd-code-interpreter.md` |\n713: | REQ-007 | Configuration | Config docs for Router, WorkloadManager, PicoD, Agentd |\n714: | REQ-008 | Deployment | Helm guide, prerequisites, multi-namespace, security |\n715: | REQ-009 | Examples | PCAP analyzer, quick start, LangChain tutorial |\n716: | REQ-010 | Navigation | Sidebar config, cross-references, index page |\n717: | REQ-011 | Quality | API coverage, build success, runnable examples |\n718: | REQ-012 | Internationalization | English primary, translation structure |\n719: | REQ-013 | Search | Search plugin configuration and indexing |\n720: \n721: **Total Requirements:** 13  \n722: **Total Scenarios:** 48\n723: \n724: ---\n725: \n726: ## Documentation File Structure\n727: \n728: ```\n729: docs/docs/\n730: ├── architecture/\n731: │   ├── overview.md                 (REQ-001)\n732: │   ├── router.md                   (REQ-002)\n733: │   ├── workloadmanager.md          (REQ-002)\n734: │   ├── picod.md                    (REQ-002)\n735: │   ├── agentd.md                   (REQ-002)\n736: │   ├── data-flow/\n737: │   │   ├── sandbox-creation.md     (REQ-003)\n738: │   │   ├── code-execution.md       (REQ-003)\n739: │   │   └── session-routing.md      (REQ-003)\n740: │   └── crd/\n741: │       ├── agent-runtime.md        (REQ-006)\n742: │       └── code-interpreter.md     (REQ-006)\n743: │\n744: ├── api/\n745: │   ├── sdk-python/\n746: │   │   ├── overview.md             (REQ-004)\n747: │   │   ├── code-interpreter-client.md (REQ-004)\n748: │   │   ├── agent-runtime-client.md    (REQ-004)\n749: │   │   ├── exceptions.md           (REQ-004)\n750: │   │   └── sessions.md             (REQ-004)\n751: │   └── client-go/\n752: │       ├── overview.md             (REQ-005)\n753: │       ├── clientset.md            (REQ-005)\n754: │       ├── agent-runtime-crud.md   (REQ-005)\n755: │       ├── code-interpreter-crud.md (REQ-005)\n756: │       ├── informer.md             (REQ-005)\n757: │       └── testing.md              (REQ-005)\n758: │\n759: ├── deployment/\n76