{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907218039,"sessionID":"ses_283af0829ffeKBpaLvjWQ0hTo4","part":{"id":"prt_d7c519e020016aGH0Xs7w7G5D4","messageID":"msg_d7c5173610013QaU445fFkBs09","sessionID":"ses_283af0829ffeKBpaLvjWQ0hTo4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ee67592ad40c4047930a7d7676572c88","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 1\n3: id: architecture-overview\n4: title: Architecture Overview\n5: description: High-level overview of AgentCube system architecture, components, and deployment topology\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Architecture Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform designed for AI agents. It provides secure, isolated execution environments for code interpreters and agent runtimes with built-in session management, authentication, and automatic cleanup.\n11: \n12: ## System Purpose\n13: \n14: AgentCube enables:\n15: \n16: - **Sandboxed Code Execution**: Execute code in isolated container environments\n17: - **Agent Runtime Management**: Deploy and manage AI agent containers\n18: - **Session Lifecycle**: Automatic session creation, tracking, and cleanup\n19: - **Secure Routing**: JWT-based authentication and traffic routing to sandbox pods\n20: - **Warm Pool Support**: Pre-warmed sandbox instances for fast startup\n21: \n22: ## System Topology\n23: \n24: ```mermaid\n25: graph TB\n26:     subgraph \"Client Layer\"\n27:         SDK[Python SDK]\n28:         GO[Go Client]\n29:     end\n30: \n31:     subgraph \"Router Layer\"\n32:         R[Router<br/>:8080]\n33:     end\n34: \n35:     subgraph \"Session Store\"\n36:         REDIS[Redis/Valkey<br/>Session Store]\n37:     end\n38: \n39:     subgraph \"Workload Management\"\n40:         WM[WorkloadManager<br/>:8080]\n41:     end\n42: \n43:     subgraph \"Kubernetes API\"\n44:         K8S[Kubernetes API<br/>CRDs, Pods, Secrets]\n45:     end\n46: \n47:     subgraph \"Sandbox Pods\"\n48:         POD1[Sandbox Pod 1<br/>+ PicoD sidecar]\n49:         POD2[Sandbox Pod 2<br/>+ PicoD sidecar]\n50:         POD3[Agent Pod<br/>Runtime]\n51:     end\n52: \n53:     subgraph \"Cleanup Controller\"\n54:         AGENTD[Agentd<br/>Idle Cleanup]\n55:     end\n56: \n57:     SDK -->|JWT Auth| R\n58:     GO -->|JWT Auth| R\n59:     R -->|Session Lookup| REDIS\n60:     R -->|Create Sandbox| WM\n61:     R -->|Proxy Traffic| POD1\n62:     R -->|Proxy Traffic| POD2\n63:     R -->|Proxy Traffic| POD3\n64:     WM -->|Create CRDs| K8S\n65:     WM -->|Create Pods| K8S\n66:     WM -->|Session Info| REDIS\n67:     AGENTD -->|Watch CRDs| K8S\n68:     AGENTD -->|Cleanup Idle| K8S\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Core Components\n72: \n73: | Component | Module | Purpose | Framework |\n74: |-----------|--------|---------|-----------|\n75: | Router | `pkg/router` | Session routing, reverse proxy, JWT validation | Gin |\n76: | WorkloadManager | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Sandbox lifecycle management | Chi |\n77: | PicoD | `pkg/picod` | Local code execution daemon | Gin |\n78: | Agentd | `pkg/agentd` | Idle cleanup controller | controller-runtime |\n79: | Store | `pkg/store` | Session storage abstraction | Redis/Valkey |\n80: \n81: ## Tech Stack\n82: \n83: | Technology | Version | Purpose |\n84: |------------|---------|---------|\n85: | Go | 1.24 | Server components runtime |\n86: | Python | ≥3.10 | CLI/SDK |\n87: | Gin | v1.x | Router HTTP framework |\n88: | Chi | v5.x | WorkloadManager HTTP framework |\n89: | Kubernetes CRDs | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | Custom resources |\n90: | Redis/Valkey | 7.x | Session state storage |\n91: | JWT | RS256 | Authentication tokens |\n92: \n93: ## Deployment Patterns\n94: \n95: ### Pattern 1: Router Deployment\n96: \n97: The Router runs as a Kubernetes Deployment, handling incoming requests:\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: apiVersion: apps/v1\n101: kind: Deployment\n102: metadata:\n103:   name: agentcube-router\n104:   namespace: agentcube-system\n105: spec:\n106:   replicas: 2\n107:   template:\n108:     spec:\n109:       containers:\n110:       - name: router\n111:         image: volcano-sh/agentcube-router:v0.2.0\n112:         ports:\n113:         - containerPort: 8080\n114:         env:\n115:         - name: STORE_ADDR\n116:           value: \"redis:6379\"\n117: ```\n118: \n119: **Resource Requirements**:\n120: - CPU: 100m-500m\n121: - Memory: 128Mi-256Mi\n122: - Replicas: 2 (recommended for HA)\n123: \n124: ### Pattern 2: WorkloadManager Deployment\n125: \n126: The WorkloadManager manages sandbox lifecycle:\n127: \n128: ```yaml\n129: apiVersion: apps/v1\n130: kind: Deployment\n131: metadata:\n132:   name: agentcube-workloadmanager\n133:   namespace: agentcube-system\n134: spec:\n135:   replicas: 1\n136:   template:\n137:     spec:\n138:       containers:\n139:       - name: workloadmanager\n140:         image: volcano-sh/agentcube-workloadmanager:v0.2.0\n141:         ports:\n142:         - containerPort: 8080\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Resource Requirements**:\n146: - CPU: 200m-1000m\n147: - Memory: 256Mi-512Mi\n148: - Replicas: 1 (singleton for consistency)\n149: \n150: ### Pattern 3: Sandbox Pods with PicoD Sidecar\n151: \n152: Sandbox pods optionally include the PicoD sidecar:\n153: \n154: ```yaml\n155: apiVersion: v1\n156: kind: Pod\n157: metadata:\n158:   name: sandbox-abc123\n159:   labels:\n160:     runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id: \"sess-abc123\"\n161: spec:\n162:   containers:\n163:   - name: main\n164:     image: python:3.11-slim\n165:     command: [\"sleep\", \"infinity\"]\n166:   - name: picod\n167:     image: volcano-sh/agentcube-picod:v0.2.0\n168:     ports:\n169:     - containerPort: 8080\n170:     volumeMounts:\n171:     - name: workspace\n172:       mountPath: /workspace\n173:   volumes:\n174:   - name: workspace\n175:     emptyDir:\n176:       sizeLimit: 1Gi\n177: ```\n178: \n179: **Resource Requirements**:\n180: - CPU: 100m-500m per container\n181: - Memory: 128Mi-512Mi per container\n182: - Workspace: 1Gi-10Gi emptyDir\n183: \n184: ### Pattern 4: Agentd Controller\n185: \n186: The Agentd controller runs with leader election:\n187: \n188: ```yaml\n189: apiVersion: apps/v1\n190: kind: Deployment\n191: metadata:\n192:   name: agentcube-agentd\n193:   namespace: agentcube-system\n194: spec:\n195:   replicas: 1\n196:   template:\n197:     spec:\n198:       containers:\n199:       - name: agentd\n200:         image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agentd:v0.2.0\n201:         args:\n202:         - --leader-election=true\n203:         - --idle-threshold=30m\n204: ```\n205: \n206: **Resource Requirements**:\n207: - CPU: 50m-200m\n208: - Memory: 64Mi-128Mi\n209: - Replicas: 1 (leader election for HA)\n210: \n211: ## Data Model\n212: \n213: ### Custom Resource Definitions\n214: \n215: AgentCube defines two main CRDs:\n216: \n217: | CRD | API Group | Purpose |\n218: |-----|-----------|---------|\n219: | AgentRuntime | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | AI agent runtime configuration |\n220: | CodeInterpreter | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | Code execution environment |\n221: \n222: ### Session State\n223: \n224: Session state is stored in Redis/Valkey with the following structure:\n225: \n226: | Key Pattern | Type | TTL | Content |\n227: |-------------|------|-----|---------|\n228: | `session:<id>` | Hash | Session timeout | Session metadata |\n229: | `session:<id>:sandbox` | String | Session timeout | Sandbox pod endpoint |\n230: \n231: ### Labels and Annotations\n232: \n233: Standard labels applied to sandbox pods:\n234: \n235: | Label | Value | Purpose |\n236: |-------|-------|---------|\n237: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | CR name | Owner reference |\n238: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter | Kind reference |\n239: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | Session ID | Active session |\n240: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | agent/code-interpreter | Type classification |\n241: \n242: ## Communication Flow\n243: \n244: ### Request Routing\n245: \n246: 1. Client sends request with JWT token\n247: 2. Router validates JWT signature\n248: 3. Router queries session store for sandbox endpoint\n249: 4. Router proxies request to sandbox pod\n250: 5. Router updates session last activity timestamp\n251: \n252: ### Sandbox Creation\n253: \n254: 1. SDK creates session request\n255: 2. Router forwards to WorkloadManager\n256: 3. WorkloadManager creates CRDs (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n257: 4. WorkloadManager creates Pod and Secret\n258: 5. WorkloadManager registers session in store\n259: 6. Router returns sandbox endpoint to client\n260: \n261: ## Security Architecture\n262: \n263: ### Authentication\n264: \n265: - JWT RS256 tokens for client authentication\n266: - Token contains: session_id, sandbox_id, namespace, name\n267: - Tokens expire with session timeout\n268: \n269: ### Network Isolation\n270: \n271: - Sandbox pods run in dedicated namespaces\n272: - Network policies restrict pod-to-pod communication\n273: - Router is the only entry point for external traffic\n274: \n275: ### RBAC\n276: \n277: - WorkloadManager requires permissions to create Pods, Secrets, CRDs\n278: - Agentd requires permissions to list and delete CRDs\n279: - Router requires read-only access to session store\n280: \n281: ## Next Steps\n282: \n283: - [Router Architecture](./router.md) - Detailed router component documentation\n284: - [WorkloadManager Architecture](./workloadmanager.md) - Sandbox lifecycle management\n285: - [PicoD Architecture](./picod.md) - Code execution daemon\n286: - [Agentd Architecture](./agentd.md) - Idle cleanup controller\n287: - [Data Flow Documentation](./data-flow/sandbox-creation.md) - Request and data flows\n\n(End of file - total 287 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 1\nid: architecture-overview\ntitle: Architecture Overview\ndescription: High-level overview of AgentCube system architecture, components, and deployment topology\n---\n\n# Architecture Overview\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform designed for AI agents. It provides secure, isolated execution environments for code interpreters and agent runtimes with built-in session management, authentication, and automatic cleanup.\n\n## System Purpose\n\nAgentCube enables:\n\n- **Sandboxed Code Execution**: Execute code in isolated container environments\n- **Agent Runtime Management**: Deploy and manage AI agent containers\n- **Session Lifecycle**: Automatic session creation, tracking, and cleanup\n- **Secure Routing**: JWT-based authentication and traffic routing to sandbox pods\n- **Warm Pool Support**: Pre-warmed sandbox instances for fast startup","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md","time":{"start":1775907218008,"end":1775907218036}}}}
